## Example 5 — Real-World: Map Scale Calculation

A map has a scale of 1 : 50,000, meaning 1 cm on the map represents 50,000 cm in reality. Two cities are 8.5 cm apart on the map. Find the actual distance in kilometers.

### Step 1: Set Up the Proportion

$$\frac{1 \text{ cm (map)}}{50{,}000 \text{ cm (real)}} = \frac{8.5 \text{ cm (map)}}{x \text{ cm (real)}}$$

### Step 2: Solve for x

$$x = 8.5 \times 50{,}000 = 425{,}000 \text{ cm}$$

### Step 3: Convert to Kilometers

$$425{,}000 \text{ cm} = \frac{425{,}000}{100{,}000} \text{ km} = 4.25 \text{ km}$$

### Step 4: Verify the Reasonableness

A scale of 1:50,000 is typical for a topographic map. 8.5 cm on such a map representing 4.25 km is a reasonable hiking distance between towns.

✅ Answer: The actual distance between the cities is **4.25 km**.

